sub_title: Director Measuring Justice at HiiL | User-friendly Justice
summary:
I am a lawyer with PhD in political science who applies creatively empirical methods to understand legal dynamics. More than 15 years of professional experience in measurement and evaluation of justice sector projects, programs and policies. Some of the countries where I worked are: Bulgaria, The Netherlands, Moldova, Ukraine, Yemen, Mali, Rwanda, Azerbaijan, Russia, Turkey, Thailand, Cambodia, Poland, Indonesia, Nicaragua, Bolivia, Georgia, Kyrgyzstan, Armenia and many more.

As Head of the Measurement&Evaluation team I help our clients through:
- Applying own methodology to quantify and understand the justice needs and experience of the people
- Developing justice and rule of law indicators
- Evaluating the impact of legal innovations

My passion is to measure people's experiences with access to justice, human rights, dispute resolution and legal empowerment.
